author: freeCodeCamp.org
description:
This course is a conceptual and architectural journey through deep learning vision models, tracing the evolution from LeNet and AlexNet to ResNet, EfficientNet, and Vision Transformers. The course explains the design philosophies behind skip connections, bottlenecks, identity preservation, depth/width trade-offs, and attention. Each chapter combines clear visuals, historical context, and side-by-side comparisons to reveal why architectures look the way they do and how they process information.

Course developed by @programmingoceanacademy 

Course notes: https://www.programming-ocean.com/knowledge-hub/cnn-architect-mind-ai-atlas.php

⭐️ Contents ⭐️
⌨️ (0:00:00) Welcoming and Introduction 
⌨️ (0:01:44) What We'll Cover Broadly 
⌨️ (0:05:34) LeNet Architecture Model 
⌨️ (0:22:51) AlexNet Architecture Model 
⌨️ (0:46:26) VGG Architecture Model 
⌨️ (1:01:41) GoogLeNet / Inception Architecture Model 
⌨️ (1:36:50) Highway Networks Architecture Model 
⌨️ (2:00:45) Pathways of Information Pre
title: Deep Learning Vision Architectures Explained – CNNs from LeNet to Vision Transformers
